    {9014,"Saving the Best for Last",60,1637,{"emulator","wago"},"A truly amazing story, $N! You have my thanks, and the heartfelt gratitude of all who were involved, I can assure you. Through your efforts we are delivered from the mistakes of our past.$B$BAs to your reward, I believe I have a few things that you have definitely earned and will truly enjoy.",nil,{16012},{{itemID=22065,count=1},{itemID=22069,count=1}},60,0,nil,"Give Mokvar your Magister's Crown and Magister's Robes.",8,128,690,nil,{16012}},
    {9015,"The Challenge",60,1584,{"emulator","wago"},"Heed me well, $N.  For the banner to work in the desired way, you will need to step into the Ring of the Law in Blackrock Depths.  Allow yourself to be sentenced by High Justice Grimstone and place the banner firmly on the ground in a sign of defiance.$B$BYour victim will not be able to restrain himself and shall enter the fray filled with a desire to fight you.  Once you obtain that which you seek, go back to Anthion.",nil,{16032},nil,58,0,{"Theldren's Team Defeated"},"Travel to the Ring of the Law in Blackrock Depths and place the Banner of Provocation in its center as you are sentenced by High Justice Grimstone.  Slay Theldren and his gladiators and return to Anthion Harmon in the Eastern Plaguelands with the first piece of Lord Valthalak's amulet.",0,nil,nil,nil,{16016}},
    {9016,"Anthion's Parting Words",60,1637,{"emulator","wago"},"Valthalak's soul was stored in this amulet.  In our greed we foolishly split it into three parts, not knowing the curse that would await us.$B$BThe only way to stop Valthalak's spell is to put the amulet back together.  Return to Mokvar and tell him that Bodley is his only hope for finding the remaining pieces.  Speak to him about any rewards you've arranged for.$B$BI, for once, shall rest in peace.  I wish you the best of luck; you shall need every bit of it!",nil,{16016},{{itemID=22107,count=1},{itemID=22111,count=1},{itemID=22112,count=1}},58,0,nil,"Return to Mokvar in Orgimmar with a set of Wildheart Boots, a Wildheart Kilt and Wildheart Spaulders.",0,1024,690,nil,{16012}},
    {9017,"Anthion's Parting Words",60,1637,{"emulator","wago"},"Valthalak's soul was stored in this amulet.  In our greed we foolishly split it into three parts, not knowing the curse that would await us.$B$BThe only way to stop Valthalak's spell is to put the amulet back together.  Return to Mokvar and tell him that Bodley is his only hope for finding the remaining pieces.  Speak to him about any rewards you've arranged for.$B$BI, for once, shall rest in peace.  I wish you the best of luck; you shall need every bit of it!",nil,{16016},{{itemID=22061,count=1},{itemID=22017,count=1},{itemID=22016,count=1}},60,0,nil,"Return to Mokvar in Orgimmar with a set of Beaststalker's Boots, Beaststalker's Pants and Beaststalker's Mantle.",0,4,690,nil,{16012}},
    {9018,"Anthion's Parting Words",60,1637,{"emulator","wago"},"Valthalak's soul was stored in this amulet.  In our greed we foolishly split it into three parts, not knowing the curse that would await us.$B$BThe only way to stop Valthalak's spell is to put the amulet back together.  Return to Mokvar and tell him that Bodley is his only hope for finding the remaining pieces.  Speak to him about any rewards you've arranged for.$B$BI, for once, shall rest in peace.  I wish you the best of luck; you shall need every bit of it!",nil,{16016},{{itemID=22064,count=1},{itemID=22067,count=1},{itemID=22068,count=1}},60,0,nil,"Return to Mokvar in Orgimmar with a set of Magister's Boots, Magister's Leggings and Magister's Mantle.",0,128,690,nil,{16012}},
