    {9269,"Atiesh, Greatstaff of the Guardian",60,-344,{"emulator","wago"},"This final task will be the most difficult of all, $N. You have faced and defeated both an Old God and the Lich King's General, but now you must face the hand of Sargeras.$B$BTake the staff to Stratholme. It is there that you will find a piece of consecrated earth: ground where the greatest knights of Lordaeron were murdered. Place the befouled staff upon the holy ground and prepare for an entity of immense power to break from within... Defeat the demonic being that controls the staff and return to me.",nil,{15192},{{itemID=22632,count=1}},60,0,{"Atiesh Cleansed"},"Anachronos at the Caverns of Time in Tanaris wants you to take Atiesh, Greatstaff of the Guardian to Stratholme and use it on Consecrated Earth. Defeat the entity that is exorcised from the staff and return to him.",0,1024,nil,nil,{15192}},
    {9270,"Atiesh, Greatstaff of the Guardian",60,-344,{"emulator","wago"},"This final task will be the most difficult of all, $N. You have faced and defeated both an Old God and the Lich King's General, but now you must face the hand of Sargeras.$B$BTake the staff to Stratholme. It is there that you will find a piece of consecrated earth: ground where the greatest knights of Lordaeron were murdered. Place the befouled staff upon the holy ground and prepare for an entity of immense power to break from within... Defeat the demonic being that controls the staff and return to me.",nil,{15192},{{itemID=22589,count=1}},60,0,{"Atiesh Cleansed"},"Anachronos at the Caverns of Time in Tanaris wants you to take Atiesh, Greatstaff of the Guardian to Stratholme and use it on Consecrated Earth. Defeat the entity that is exorcised from the staff and return to him.",0,128,nil,nil,{15192}},
    {9271,"Atiesh, Greatstaff of the Guardian",60,-344,{"emulator","wago"},"This final task will be the most difficult of all, $N. You have faced and defeated both an Old God and the Lich King's General, but now you must face the hand of Sargeras.$B$BTake the staff to Stratholme. It is there that you will find a piece of consecrated earth: ground where the greatest knights of Lordaeron were murdered. Place the befouled staff upon the holy ground and prepare for an entity of immense power to break from within... Defeat the demonic being that controls the staff and return to me.",nil,{15192},{{itemID=22630,count=1}},60,0,{"Atiesh Cleansed"},"Anachronos at the Caverns of Time in Tanaris wants you to take Atiesh, Greatstaff of the Guardian to Stratholme and use it on Consecrated Earth. Defeat the entity that is exorcised from the staff and return to him.",0,256,nil,nil,{15192}},
    {9272,"Dressing the Part",55,33,{"emulator","wago"},nil,nil,{2546},{{itemID=22746,count=1}},49,0,nil,nil,8,nil,nil,nil,{2546}},
    {9274,"Spirits of the Drowned",12,3433,{"emulator","wago"},"The lake to the north has been haunted by the ghosts of my ancestors for as long as I can remember, $N.  The poor souls were victims of a tragic incident in which scores of them drowned at the bottom of the lake.$B$BThe details of the event are mostly forgotten, but their haunting cries serve as a constant reminder of their curse.$B$BIf you're up to the task, I want you to go to the lake and put an end to their suffering, $N.  You will have my gratitude as well as theirs... I'm sure.",nil,{16462},nil,9,500,nil,"Ranger Krenn'an, at the Farstrider Enclave in the Ghostlands, wants you to kill 8 Vengeful Apparitions and 8 Ravening Apparitions in the nearby lake.",136,nil,690,nil,{16462}},
    {9275,"A Little Dash of Seasoning",19,3433,{"emulator","wago"},"I'm on loan to the Farstriders in an attempt to help with their troll difficulties. I believe that I have a solution to their problem.$B$BAt my disposal are a number of potent poisons. The trolls, as you know, are living creatures and therefore must eat. If we combine my poison with their food... well, I'm sure that the results will be entertaining!$B$BCare to help rid us of the Shadowpine trolls at Zeb'Nowa to the south? The camp straddles both the north and south sides of the road to Zul'Aman.",nil,{16464},nil,16,1100,{"Poison the Raw Meat Rack","Poison the Smoked Meat Rack","Poison the Fresh Fish Rack"},"Poison the Troll foodstuff at the camps in Zeb'Nowa and then return to Apothecary Venustus at the Farstrider Enclave in the Ghostlands.",128,nil,690,nil,{16464}},
    {9276,"Attack on Zeb'Tela",18,3433,{"emulator","wago"},"Our resources are spread pretty thin here, $c, so your help is going to be invaluable.  The captain has tasked me with overseeing the harassment of the local Shadowpine troll camps. We have a policy of keeping them off balance until the day when we can launch a brutal offensive to wipe them out.$B$BUntil then, we need all of the volunteers that we can get so that those Shadowpine troll numbers are decreased.$B$BThink you could head east to Zeb'Tela and hurt them a little?",nil,{16463},nil,15,1000,nil,"Kill 8 Shadowpine Shadowcasters and 8 Shadowpine Headhunters, and return to Farstrider Solanna at Farstrider Enclave in the Ghostlands.",136,nil,690,nil,{16463}},
    {9277,"Assault on Zeb'Nowa",19,3433,{"emulator","wago"},"Time for something a little more challenging. Zeb'Nowa, to the south, is where the more powerful Shadowpine trolls make their home. In our continuing effort to keep the troll numbers to a minimum I'm dispatching you to go down there and assail them by whatever means you have at your disposal.$B$BWhat do you say, $N? Ready to deal with some more trolls?",nil,{16463},nil,15,1100,nil,"Kill 10 Shadowpine Catlords and 10 Shadowpine Hexxers, and return to Farstrider Solanna at the Farstrider Enclave in the Ghostlands.",136,nil,690,nil,{16463}},
    {9278,"Welcome!",1,3526,{"emulator","wago"},"Welcome to the World of Warcraft!$B$BAs special thanks for purchasing the World of Warcraft Collector's Edition, turn in this gift voucher to Jaeleil at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.  You'll then be given a gift: a little companion to join you on your quest for adventure and glory.$B$BThanks again, and enjoy your stay in the World of Warcraft!",nil,nil,nil,1,0,nil,"Bring the Ammen Vale Gift Voucher to Jaeleil inside the ship at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.",128,nil,nil,nil,{16476}},
    {9279,"You Survived!",1,3526,{"emulator","wago"},"Nevermind my injuries, $g brother : sister;. It's a miracle that any of us are alive!$b$bIt didn't look like you'd pull through; you've been in suspension for weeks.$B$BSomething happened and the Exodar crashed. Many have died.$B$BBut I'm relieved that you are alive, $N. With you leading our efforts, I'm sure we'll get to safety soon! Proenitus asked me to send you to him when you awoke. He's waiting for you at the bottom of the hill. Just follow the path southwest.",nil,{16475},nil,1,0,nil,"Speak with Proenitus at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.",136,nil,1024,nil,{16477}},
    {9280,"Replenishing the Healing Crystals",1,3526,{"emulator","wago"},"Our immediate concern is the depleted state of our healing crystals.  We must replenish them quickly!$B$BUnfortunately, the only way to do this at this point is to extract the blood from the local vale moths.  Their blood will make for a suitable substitute.$B$BThe moths can be found in many places around the vale, but they are mostly concentrated in the northwest.",nil,{16477},nil,1,15,nil,"Acquire 8 Vials of Moth Blood from the nearby Vale Moths and give them to Proenitus at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.",136,nil,1024,nil,{16477}},
    {9281,"Clearing the Way",18,3433,{"emulator","wago"},"Magister Kaendris sent me down here to clear the area of any hostile wildlife.  Once this area is secured, the magisters plan to turn it into some sort of advance outpost against the Scourge.$B$BNow if there's one thing I've learned as an apprentice it's to delegate responsibility - especially in matters that endanger one's life!$B$BIf you're interested, I'll pay you well to kill the greater spindlewebs and ghostclaw ravagers to the west and south of here.",nil,{16480},nil,15,2000,nil,"Apprentice Vor'el at Andilien Estate in the Ghostlands wants you to slay 10 Greater Spindlewebs and 10 Ghostclaw Ravagers.",136,nil,690,nil,{16480}},
    {9282,"The Farstrider Enclave",16,3433,{"emulator","wago"},"Magisters and Farstriders may not see eye to eye all the time, $N.  When it comes to Dar'Khan, however, we're all in agreement that a way must be found to defeat him and his legions.$B$BRanger Vynna, at the Farstrider Enclave northeast of here, has come across important information regarding our enemy.  Speak to her and see if you can be of assistance.",nil,{16239},nil,15,0,nil,"Magister Kaendris, at the Sanctum of the Sun, wants you to talk to Ranger Vynna at the Farstrider Enclave in the Ghostlands.",136,nil,690,nil,{16203}},
    {9283,"Rescue the Survivors!",2,3526,{"emulator","wago"},"The healing crystals are replenished, but that is not the only way we can help the injured. All draenei can tap the gift of the Naaru to heal. You must use this ability to heal one of the crash survivors.$b$bYou'll find most of the survivors in the areas to the west and northwest, but the crash scattered us all over the vale.$b$bThe survivors have suffered from exposure to the irradiated power crystals, so you should be able to find them by the red glow that surround them.$B$BYou must save them, $N.",nil,{16502},{{itemID=23389,count=1}},1,65,{"Draenei Survivors Saved"},"Use your Gift of the Naaru ability on one of the Draenei Survivors spread throughout Ammen Vale, then return to Zalduun at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.",128,nil,1024,nil,{16502}},
    {9284,"Aldor Faction Test",60,0,{"emulator"},nil,nil,nil,nil,1,0,nil,nil,136},
    {9285,"Consortium Faction Test",60,0,{"emulator"},nil,nil,nil,nil,1,0,nil,nil,136},
    {9286,"Scryers Faction Test",60,0,{"emulator"},nil,nil,nil,nil,1,0,nil,nil,136},
    {9287,"Paladin Training",2,-141,{"emulator","wago"},nil,nil,{16501},nil,1,0,nil,nil,128,2,1024,nil,{16501}},
    {9288,"Hunter Training",2,-261,{"emulator","wago"},nil,nil,{16499},nil,1,0,nil,nil,128,4,1024,nil,{16499}},
    {9289,"Warrior Training",2,-81,{"emulator","wago"},nil,nil,{16503},nil,1,0,nil,nil,128,1,1024,nil,{16503}},
    {9290,"Mage Training",2,-161,{"emulator","wago"},nil,nil,nil,nil,1,0,nil,nil,128,128,1024},
    {9291,"Priest Training",2,-262,{"emulator","wago"},nil,nil,{16502},nil,1,0,nil,nil,128,16,1024,nil,{16502}},
    {9292,"Cracked Necrotic Crystal",-1,-368,{"emulator","wago"},"On the corpse of the fallen abomination, you discover a cracked crystal, slowly pulsing with necrotic energy.",nil,{16431},nil,1,0,nil,"Bring the Cracked Necrotic Crystal to Lieutenant Orrin outside the gates of Stormwind.",0,nil,1101,nil,{16478}},
    {9293,"What Must Be Done...",2,3526,{"emulator","wago"},"The nearby lake has been contaminated by one of the ship's power crystals.  Many of the plants and animals of Ammen Vale have been mutated because of this.$B$BI have a theory on how to heal the lake, but I must have samples from the mutated lashers for analysis.  They can be found to the west in the Ammen Fields.$B$BWill you help me, $c?",nil,{16514},nil,1,35,nil,"Gather 10 Lasher Samples and return them to Botanist Taerix at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.",136,nil,1101,nil,{16514}},
    {9294,"Healing the Lake",3,3526,{"emulator","wago"},"Thank goodness, I think it'll work!  I have an agent for you to spread at Silverline Lake to the south.  It will neutralize the effects of the irradiated ship's power crystal that fell there.$B$BSwim out and scatter the neutralizing agent near it.  Don't worry, you won't be exposed long enough to become irradiated.",nil,{16514},nil,1,0,{"Disperse the Neutralizing Agent"},"Disperse the Neutralizing Agent at the Irradiated Power Crystal, then return to Botanist Taerix at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.",128,nil,1101,nil,{16514}},
    {9295,"Letter from the Front",-1,-368,{"emulator","wago"},"You found this letter on one of the many Scourge minions you've slain. From its appearance and smell, it has been with the undead for some time. Perhaps someone at Light's Hope Chapel would be interested in examining it further...",nil,nil,nil,45,0,nil,"Take the Torn Letter to the Keeper of the Rolls at Light's Hope Chapel in the Eastern Plaguelands.",0,nil,nil,nil,{16281}},
    {9298,nil,nil,nil,{"wago"}},
    {9299,"Note from the Front",-1,-368,{"emulator","wago"},"You found this letter on one of the many Scourge minions you've slain. From its appearance and smell, it has been with the undead for some time. Perhaps someone at Light's Hope Chapel would be interested in examining it further...",nil,nil,nil,45,0,nil,"Take the Careworn Note to the Keeper of the Rolls at Light's Hope Chapel in the Eastern Plaguelands.",0,nil,nil,nil,{16281}},
    {9300,"Page from the Front",-1,-368,{"emulator","wago"},"You found this letter on one of the many Scourge minions you've slain. From its appearance and smell, it has been with the undead for some time. Perhaps someone at Light's Hope Chapel would be interested in examining it further...",nil,nil,nil,45,0,nil,"Take the Ragged Page to the Keeper of the Rolls at Light's Hope Chapel in the Eastern Plaguelands.",0,nil,nil,nil,{16281}},
    {9301,"Envelope from the Front",-1,-368,{"emulator","wago"},"You found this letter on one of the many Scourge minions you've slain. From its appearance and smell, it has been with the undead for some time. Perhaps someone at Light's Hope Chapel would be interested in examining it further...",nil,nil,nil,45,0,nil,"Take the Bloodstained Envelope to the Keeper of the Rolls at Light's Hope Chapel in the Eastern Plaguelands.",0,nil,nil,nil,{16281}},
    {9302,"Missive from the Front",-1,-368,{"emulator","wago"},"You found this letter on one of the many Scourge minions you've slain. From its appearance and smell, it has been with the undead for some time. Perhaps someone at Light's Hope Chapel would be interested in examining it further...",nil,nil,nil,45,0,nil,"Take the Crumpled Missive to the Keeper of the Rolls at Light's Hope Chapel in the Eastern Plaguelands.",0,nil,nil,nil,{16281}},
    {9303,"Inoculation",4,3526,{"emulator","wago"},"Zhanaa needs our help to salvage parts from the Exodar.  Taerix prepared an inoculum that can be given to the Nestlewood owlkin that live in the area of a lot of the salvage.$B$BJust get close to the unaffected ones and use the crystal on them.  Unfortunately, you'll have to kill the others.  You'll find the owlkin at Nestlewood Thicket and Nestlewood Hills to the southeast.",nil,{16535},{{itemID=118,count=3}},2,150,{"Nestlewood Owlkin inoculated"},"Use the Inoculating Crystal on 6 Nestlewood Owlkin. Then return to Vindicator Aldar at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.",128,nil,1101,nil,{16535}},
    {9304,"Document from the Front",-1,-368,{"emulator","wago"},"You found this letter on one of the many Scourge minions you've slain. From its appearance and smell, it has been with the undead for some time. Perhaps someone at Light's Hope Chapel would be interested in examining it further...",nil,nil,nil,45,0,nil,"Take the Smudged Document to the Keeper of the Rolls at Light's Hope Chapel in the Eastern Plaguelands.",0,nil,nil,nil,{16281}},
    {9305,"Spare Parts",4,3526,{"emulator","wago"},"We managed to recover a damaged holographic emitter from the crash. If we repair it, we'll have a chance to find other survivors outside of Ammen Vale.$B$BThere were devices from the ship that could be salvaged for spare parts in the area, but the local owlkin carried them off before we could get to them. $B$B$N, you must go south to Nestlewood Thicket and Hills to find the spare parts.",nil,{17071},nil,2,0,nil,"Collect 4 Emitter Spare Parts and then return to Technician Zhanaa at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.",136,nil,1101,nil,{17071}},
    {9306,nil,nil,nil,{"wago"}},
    {9307,nil,nil,nil,{"wago"}},
    {9308,nil,nil,nil,{"wago"}},
    {9309,"The Missing Scout",5,3526,{"emulator","wago"},"We now have several separate confirmations of unusual activity up on the Shadow Ridge.$B$BThis is disturbing; we thought that the scouting missions already undertaken had been thorough. One of my scouts hasn't reported back yet.$B$B$C, I need you to head southwest to the other side of Silverline Lake and find Tolaan, and see what has delayed him.",nil,{16535},nil,2,0,nil,"Find and speak with Tolaan at Shadow Ridge in Ammen Vale.",136,nil,1101,nil,{16546}},
    {9310,"Faint Necrotic Crystal",-1,-368,{"emulator","wago"},"On the corpse of the fallen wight, you find a crystal that is faintly radiating necrotic energy.",nil,{16531},nil,1,0,nil,"Bring the Faint Necrotic Crystal to Lieutenant Rukag in the courtyard of the Undercity.",0,nil,690,nil,{16494}},
    {9311,"Blood Elf Spy",5,3526,{"emulator","wago"},"I have a plan. We must kill their leader. Without their master, perhaps they will retreat to regroup. We just need to buy time until the repairs are completed.$b$bThen Vindicator Aldar must know of this. Kill the surveyor, then return and tell him what we've found.",nil,{16546},nil,2,300,nil,"Slay Surveyor Candress and then inform Vindicator Aldar at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.",136,nil,1101,nil,{16535}},
    {9312,"The Emitter",5,3526,{"emulator","wago"},"$N, while you were out investigating the Shadow Ridge, Zhanaa here has been going on about the holographic emitter.  You might want to speak with her.",nil,{16535},nil,3,0,nil,"Speak with Technician Zhanaa at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.",136,nil,1101,nil,{17071}},
    {9313,"Travel to Azure Watch",5,3524,{"emulator","wago"},"By all that is good, $N, you must go at once to this Azure Watch and speak with Dyvuun!$B$BThere is a path that leads west off of this tiny isle.  Follow it and cross the Crystalbrook River to arrive on the larger part of the isle.  Continue to follow the path and you should find Azure Watch.$B$BSee if you can convince them to send us some aid and supplies.  The rest of us will follow when we can.$B$BThank you, we wouldn't have made it without you!",nil,{17071},nil,2,0,nil,"Speak with Technician Dyvuun at Azure Watch on Azuremyst Isle.",136,nil,1101,nil,{16551}},
    {9314,"Word from Azure Watch",5,3524,{"emulator","wago"},"$C! A couple mutated beasts jumped me and my leg is injured.$B$BI was sent on a scouting mission from Azure Watch after we received word from Zhanaa. Please, could you go speak with Caregiver Chellan in my stead? She needs to know how many people to expect in Azure Watch. Just cross the Crystalbrook River here and continue following the road until you get to Azure Watch.$B$BBe sure to ask her for a place for yourself to stay in.",nil,{16554},nil,1,0,nil,"Speak with Caregiver Chellan at Azure Watch on Azuremyst Isle.",128,nil,1101,nil,{16553}},
    {9315,"Anok'suten",11,3433,{"emulator","wago"},"Come closer, I am ... dying.$B$BI was sent here ... to slay these nerubians, but Vandril didn't ... know that they have a leader.$B$B<The dying blood elf coughs up a good amount of blood.>$B$BYou must find and ... slay Anok'suten.  Get help.  She wanders around ... Suncrown Village.",nil,{16601},nil,9,400,nil,"Slay Anok'suten and return to Arcanist Vandril at Tranquillien in the Ghostlands.",136,nil,690,nil,{16197}},
    {9316,nil,nil,nil,{"wago"}},
    {9317,"Consecrated Sharpening Stones",-1,0,{"emulator"},nil,nil,{16786},{{itemID=23122,count=1}},50,0,nil,nil,8,nil,1101,nil,{16786}},
    {9318,"Blessed Wizard Oil",-1,0,{"emulator"},nil,nil,{16786},{{itemID=23123,count=1}},50,0,nil,nil,8,nil,1101,nil,{16786}},
    {9319,"A Light in Dark Places",-1,-369,{"emulator","wago"},"We are not the only ones who celebrate this holiday, $n. All creatures, all cultures, are touched by the flame. Even in the darkest places, the fires are being lit.$b$bIf you wish to see them for yourself, travel into the depths. Seek out the bonfires burning within Stratholme, Scholomance, among the ogres of Dire Maul, and the halls of Blackrock Spire itself; I will await your return.",nil,{16788},{{itemID=23083,count=1},{itemID=23247,count=10}},50,0,{"Flame of Blackrock Spire","Flame of Dire Maul","Flame of the Scholomance","Flame of Stratholme"},"Find and touch the bonfires located within Blackrock Spire, Dire Maul, Scholomance, and Stratholme, then return to the Festival Flamekeeper.",8,nil,nil,nil,{16788}},
    {9320,"Major Mana Potion",-1,0,{"emulator"},nil,nil,{16787},{{itemID=13444,count=1}},50,0,nil,nil,8,nil,690,nil,{16787}},
    {9321,"Major Healing Potion",-1,0,{"emulator"},nil,nil,{16786},{{itemID=13446,count=1}},50,0,nil,nil,8,nil,1101,nil,{16786}},
    {9322,"Wild Fires in Kalimdor",-1,-369,{"emulator","wago"},"The Midsummer Fire Festival is celebrated everywhere in Azeroth, and the diverse land of Kalimdor is no exception. You look fit to travel -- perhaps a journey is in order.$b$bMidsummer cannot be truly appreciated unless you've seen the blistering blue fires abroad. The celebrants have lit fires in chilly western Winterspring, northeastern Azshara, near Valor's Rest in the wastes of Silithus, and by the entrance to lush Un'Goro. Return once your journey is complete.",nil,{16788},{{itemID=23379,count=1},{itemID=23247,count=10}},1,0,nil,"Visit the Midsummer camps located in Azshara, Silithus, Un'Goro Crater, and Winterspring, then return to the Festival Flamekeeper.",8,nil,nil,nil,{16788}},
    {9323,"Wild Fires in the Eastern Kingdoms",-1,-369,{"emulator","wago"},"Our celebration of the flame is spread throughout the land, $c. Not a single place remains untouched by the heat of this holiday, and the strongest fires burn a brilliant blue. Seek them out.$b$bYou'll find one just north of Blackrock Spire. The others are located deep within the Eastern Plaguelands near a decrepit town, along the road to the cliffs within the mountainous Hinterlands, and on the way to the Dark Portal within the Blasted Lands.$b$b Return once your journey is done.",nil,{16788},{{itemID=23324,count=1},{itemID=23247,count=10}},1,0,nil,"Visit the Fire Festival camps located in Blasted Lands, Eastern Plaguelands, the Hinterlands and Searing Gorge, then speak with the Festival Flamekeeper.",8,nil,nil,nil,{16788}},
    {9324,"Stealing Orgrimmar's Flame",-1,-369,{"emulator","wago"},"This flame, stolen from the heart of Orgrimmar itself, floods you with warmth. This raw power is foreign to you, but the Loremaster might know more...",nil,nil,{{itemID=23247,count=25}},50,0,nil,"Return the Flame of Orgrimmar to the Festival Loremaster.",0,nil,1101,nil,{16817}},
    {9325,"Stealing Thunder Bluff's Flame",-1,-369,{"emulator","wago"},"This flame, stolen from the shaman of Thunder Bluff, floods you with warmth. This raw power is foreign to you, but the Loremaster might know more...",nil,nil,{{itemID=23247,count=25}},50,0,nil,"Return the Flame of Thunder Bluff to the Festival Loremaster.",0,nil,1101,nil,{16817}},
    {9326,"Stealing the Undercity's Flame",-1,-369,{"emulator","wago"},"This flame, stolen from the ruins above the Undercity, floods you with warmth. This raw power is foreign to you, but the Loremaster might know more...",nil,nil,{{itemID=23247,count=25}},50,0,nil,"Return the Flame of the Undercity to the Festival Loremaster.",0,nil,1101,nil,{16817}},
    {9327,"The Forsaken",10,3433,{"emulator","wago"},"I know it seems strange, but these Forsaken are here to help. You should speak with their leader, High Executor Mavren. He's in the tower on the west side of town.$B$BAnd, $c, when you're done talking with him return to me; I have something dire that needs to be dealt with immediately!",nil,{16197},nil,9,0,nil,"Speak with High Executor Mavren at Tranquillien in the Ghostlands.",136,nil,512,nil,{16252}},
    {9328,"Hero of the Sin'dorei",21,3433,{"emulator","wago"},"This is the beginning of a new chapter in the history of our race, $N.  Our lands will be reclaimed and we shall cement our bond with Sylvanas and her allies.$B$BTake the traitor's head to Regent Lord Lor'themar Theron in Silvermoon City.  He'll be eager to hear the news.",nil,{16239},nil,15,0,nil,"Take Dar'Khan's Head to Lor'themar Theron in Silvermoon City.",128,nil,512,nil,{16802}},
    {9329,"The Forsaken",10,3433,{"emulator","wago"},"I know it seems strange, but the Forsaken are here to help. You should speak with their leader, High Executor Mavren.  He's in the tower on the west side of town.$B$BAnd, $c, when you're done talking with him return to me; I have something dire that needs to be dealt with immediately!",nil,{16197},nil,9,0,nil,"Speak with High Executor Mavren at Tranquillien in the Ghostlands.",136,nil,178,nil,{16252}},
    {9330,"Stealing Stormwind's Flame",-1,-369,{"emulator","wago"},"This flame, stolen from the heart of Stormwind itself, floods you with warmth. This raw power is foreign to you, but the Talespinner might know more...",nil,nil,{{itemID=23247,count=25}},50,0,nil,"Return the Flame of Stormwind to the Festival Talespinner.",0,nil,690,nil,{16818}},
    {9331,"Stealing Ironforge's Flame",-1,-369,{"emulator","wago"},"This flame, stolen from the heart of Ironforge itself, floods you with warmth. This raw power is foreign to you, but the Talespinner might know more...",nil,nil,{{itemID=23247,count=25}},50,0,nil,"Return the Flame of Ironforge to the Festival Talespinner.",0,nil,690,nil,{16818}},
    {9332,"Stealing Darnassus's Flame",-1,-369,{"emulator","wago"},"This flame, stolen from the shores of Teldrassil, floods you with warmth. This raw power is foreign to you, but the Talespinner might know more...",nil,nil,{{itemID=23247,count=25}},50,0,nil,"Return the Flame of Darnassus to the Festival Talespinner.",0,nil,690,nil,{16818}},
